OL,7,FThe Government has scrapped its
OL,8,Fcontroversial Schools Bill as part of
OL,9,Fefforts to focus on the effects of the
OL,10,Fcurrent economic crisis.
OL,12,FThe Bill, launched in May, formed part
OL,13,Fof Boris Johnson's drive to have all
OL,14,Fschools in England join an academy
OL,15,Ftrust by 2030, and included the
OL,16,Fprovision of a new register for
OL,17,Fchildren who are homeschooled.
OL,19,FThe legislation would also have granted
OL,20,Fmore powers to Ofsted, the schools
OL,21,Finspector.
OL,3,CHomeschooling register and extra powers
OL,4,Cfor Ofsted are dropped as Schools Bill
OL,5,Cis scrapped
